<dl id="n36037a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36037a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36037a"> 37(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Merchant Maiden / Burgesses</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Even earlier than Heriot&apos;s hospital was the <mark>Merchant Maiden hospital</mark>, dating from 1605, which gave to the daughters of merchants similar advantages to those which Heriot&apos;s secured for <mark>burgesses</mark>&apos; sons. <small> &ldquo;EDINBURGH&rdquo; <a name="EBED" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBED"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 942b</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
